You configure the components of Edge System by editing or creating configuration files, saving them to your local device, and then making REST requests to the provided endpoints to write them to the correct location in Edge System. Alternatively, you can configure the components of Edge System through command-line (Windows) or terminal (Linux).
	
•	To view help for Edge System components, run this command:

OSIsoft.Data.System.Host.exe help system components

•	To view all configured facets of the Edge System, run this command:

.\OSIsoft.Data.System.Host.exe configuration system



Configure components using REST

It is recommended that you then delete all configuration files from your local device, both for space considerations, and to protect any sensitive information that they could contain.
Edge System stores configuration parameters in the System_Components.json file located in:
•	Windows: %ProgramData%/OSIsoft/EdgeSystem/Configuration
•	Linux: /usr/share/OSIsoft/EdgeSystem/Configuration
Configuration parameters for Edge System components
Parameter
	
Description
ComponentId
	
Required. The ID of the component. It can be any alphanumeric string, for example Storage.
ComponentType
	
Required. The type of the component, for example EDS.Component.
There are three types of components: EDS, Modbus TCP connectivity, and OPC UA connectivity.

1. 	
In any text editor, open System_Components.json.
The recommended text editor for Linux is nano.
2. 	
Remove, add, or edit components as needed.
	
You can add multiple Modbus TCP and OPC UA connectivity components.
Default configuration with all components:

{ "ComponentConfigurations": [ { "ComponentId": "OpcUa1", "ComponentType": "OpcUa" }, { "ComponentId": "Modbus1", "ComponentType": "Modbus" }, { "ComponentId": "Storage", "ComponentType": "EDS.Component" } ] }

3. 	
Save and copy the file to all devices running Edge System.
4. 	
Use any REST client and make a request using the following:
•	Method: POST
•	Endpoint: http://localhost:5590/api/v1/configuration/system
•	Header: Content-Type application/json
•	Body: System_Components.json
Example using cURL:

curl -v -d "@System_Components.json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -X POST http://localhost:5590/api/v1/configuration/system

HTTP status 204 indicates a successful transaction and the Edge System components are configured.


Configure components on Windows

This procedure describes how to configure Edge System components using command prompt.

1. 	
Open a command prompt.
2. 	
Navigate to the Edge System installation directory: %Program Files%/OSIsoft/EdgeSystem.
3. 	
To configure a component, run this command:

.\OSIsoft.Data.System.Host.exe configuration system components componentId=componentId componentType=componentType

4. 	
To view configured components, run this command:

.\OSIsoft.Data.System.Host.exe configuration system components


Configure components on Linux

1. 	
Start a terminal.
2. 	
Navigate to the Edge System installation directory: /opt/EdgeSystem.
3. 	
To configure components, run this command:

./OSIsoft.Data.System.Host configuration system components componentId=componentId componentType=componentType

4. 	
To view configured components, run this command:

./OSIsoft.Data.System.Host configuration system components
